
[1]contentious

   CONTENTIOUS, a.

   1. Apt to contend; given to angry debate; quarrelsome; perverse.

   A continual dropping in a rainy day, and a contentious woman are alike.
   Proverbs 27.

   2. Relating to contention in law; relating to litigation; having power
   to decide causes between contending parties; as a court of contentious
   jurisdiction.

   3. Exciting or adapted to provoke contention or disputes; as a
   contentious subject.
